## Phase 2 — Parallel Feature Development (2:00–5:00)

Once the API is confirmed working, everyone works in parallel.

---

### 🟣 Member 1 — pip Package (2 hours)

Now that the backend is live, package the CLI for `pip install`.

#### Create Package Structure
```
neurotidy-package/
├── pyproject.toml
├── README.md
├── LICENSE
└── src/
    └── neurotidy/
        ├── __init__.py
        ├── cli.py          ← Refactored from cli/neurotidy.py
        └── client.py       ← API call logic
```

#### `pyproject.toml`
```toml
[build-system]
requires = ["setuptools>=61.0"]
build-backend = "setuptools.backends._legacy:_Backend"

[project]
name = "neurotidy"
version = "0.1.0"
description = "AI-Powered Python & Deep Learning Code Analyzer"
readme = "README.md"
requires-python = ">=3.8"
dependencies = ["requests>=2.28.0"]

[project.scripts]
neurotidy = "neurotidy.cli:main"
```

#### Test it locally
```powershell
pip install -e .
neurotidy explain tests/sample_code.py --mode beginner
neurotidy analyze tests/sample_code.py
```

> [!TIP]
> You don't need to publish to PyPI for the hackathon. Just showing `pip install -e .` works locally is enough. You can also create a GitHub Release with `.whl` file for download.

